# 🌤 Weather Image Classification – Microservices Architecture

## Overview

This project is a **distributed machine learning system** for weather image classification, built using a **microservices architecture** with Docker.

It combines:

* Deep Learning (ResNet50 – Transfer Learning)
* Scala Microservices (data processing & orchestration)
* FastAPI (ML inference API)
* PostgreSQL (storage & analytics)
* Streamlit (interactive frontend)

---

## Features

* Image classification (11 weather categories)
* Real-time prediction via API
* Microservices architecture (Scala + Python)
* Fully containerized with Docker
* Prediction history & statistics
* Model accuracy ~98%

---

## Architecture

```
                ┌──────────────┐
                │  Streamlit   │
                │  Frontend    │
                └──────┬───────┘
                       │ HTTP
                       ▼
                ┌──────────────┐
                │     MS2      │
                │ Prediction   │
                │   (Scala)    │
                └──────┬───────┘
                       │ HTTP
                       ▼
                ┌──────────────┐
                │   FastAPI    │
                │   ML Model   │
                └──────┬───────┘
                       │
                       ▼
                ┌──────────────┐
                │ PostgreSQL   │
                │  Database    │
                └──────────────┘

        ┌──────────────┐
        │     MS1      │
        │ Preprocessing│
        │   (Scala)    │
        └──────────────┘
```

---

## Microservices

### MS1 – Preprocessing (Scala + Spark)

* Reads raw images
* Converts to Parquet format
* Prepares data for inference

---

### MS2 – Prediction (Scala)

* Receives images from frontend
* Calls ML API
* Stores predictions in PostgreSQL

---

### API – Machine Learning (FastAPI)

* Loads trained ResNet50 model
* Performs inference
* Returns predictions (JSON)

---

### Frontend – Streamlit

* Upload images
* Display predictions
* Show statistics & history

---

## Database

PostgreSQL stores:

* predictions
* confidence scores
* model metadata
* timestamps

---

## Model

* Architecture: **ResNet50**
* Technique: Transfer Learning + Fine-tuning
* Input size: 64x64
* Classes: 11 weather types

### Classes:

```
dew, fogsmog, frost, glaze, hail,
lightning, rain, rainbow, rime,
sandstorm, snow
```

---

## Docker Setup

### Requirements

* Docker
* Docker Compose

---

## Run the project

```bash
docker-compose down -v
docker-compose build --no-cache
docker-compose up
```

---

## Access services

| Service  | URL                          |
| -------- | ---------------------------- |
| Frontend | http://localhost:8501        |
| API      | http://localhost:8000/health |
| MS2      | http://localhost:9001/health |

---

## Project Structure

```
projet_docker/
│
├── api/                # FastAPI ML service
├── microservice1/      # Scala preprocessing
├── microservice2/      # Scala prediction service
├── frontend/           # Streamlit UI
├── data/               # Input / parquet data
├── models/             # ML model
├── docker-compose.yml
├── .env
└── README.md
```

---

## Environment Variables

Configured via `.env`:

```
DB_HOST=postgres
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=weather_db
DB_USER=weather_user
DB_PASSWORD=weather_pass

API_HOST=api
API_PORT=8000

MS2_HOST=ms2
MS2_PORT=9001

MODEL_PATH=/app/models/model.h5
```

---

